zimnox.borderless

Class BorderlessScene

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Scene
      • zimnox.borderless.BorderlessScene
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.event.EventTarget

    public class BorderlessScene
extends javafx.scene.Scene
    Creates an undecorated scene with resize controls and drop shadow for JavaFX applications. Based on the code from https://github.com/goxr3plus/FX-BorderlessScene
    Version:
    2019.5.16
    Author:
    Phaelax

    • Method Detail

      • maximize

        public void maximize()
        With an undecorated stage, you must add your own buttons for minimizing, maximizing, and closing the application. To minimize the application you can use stage.setIconified(true); To maximize, call this method. It acts as a toggle so you don't need to worry about the application's maximize state yourself. The stage will match the screen size (also accounts for multiple monitors), disable resizing, and disable the shadow until the method is called again.
